
                   <p style="text-align: center">
                       <b>Title:</b> 3. Enter the following information for the KMS and the StorageGRID client you configured in that KMS.<br>
                       <b>Bounding box:</b> x1=184, y1=169, x2=1566, y2=1647
                   </p>
                   <div align="center"><table border="1" class="dataframe">
  <thead>
    <tr style="text-align: right;">
      <th></th>
      <th>0</th>
      <th>1</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th>0</th>
      <td>Field</td>
      <td>Description</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>1</th>
      <td>KMS name</td>
      <td>A descriptive name to help you identify this KMS. Must be between 1\nand 64 characters.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>2</th>
      <td>Key name</td>
      <td>The exact key alias for the StorageGRID client in the KMS. Must be\nbetween 1 and 255 characters.\nNote: If you haven’t created a key using your KMS product, you’ll be\nprompted to have StorageGRID create the key.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>3</th>
      <td>Manages keys for</td>
      <td>The StorageGRID site that will be associated with this KMS. If\npossible, you should configure any site-specific key management\nservers before configuring a default KMS that applies to all sites not\nmanaged by another KMS.\n• Select a site if this KMS will manage encryption keys for the\nappliance nodes at a specific site.\n• Select Sites not managed by another KMS (default KMS) to\nconfigure a default KMS that will apply to any sites that don’t have\na dedicated KMS and to any sites you add in subsequent\nexpansions.\nNote: A validation error will occur when you save the KMS\nconfiguration if you select a site that was previously encrypted by\nthe default KMS but you did not provide the current version of\noriginal encryption key to the new KMS.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>4</th>
      <td>Port</td>
      <td>The port the KMS server uses for Key Management Interoperability\nProtocol (KMIP) communications. Defaults to 5696, which is the KMIP\nstandard port.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <th>5</th>
      <td>Hostname</td>
      <td>The fully qualified domain name or IP address for the KMS.\nNote: The Subject Alternative Name (SAN) field of the server\ncertificate must include the FQDN or IP address you enter here.\nOtherwise, StorageGRID will not be able to connect to the KMS or to\nall servers in a KMS cluster.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table></div>
